Description: Body sherd of East Greek grey ware pottery dinos; dark grey fabric with mica inclusions; dark grey slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Sherd belongs to the same vessel as British Museum 1888,0601.634, which was analysed with NAA by Hans Mommsen (Bonn) and the fabric (sample NAUK 62) was determined to belong to group B-Troy. the origin of the fabric has been determined as from the region of the Troad.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.061)
